ownedComment.body: I like how double cliking on action opens spec for activity, and adding parameter nodes directly in activity spec. But, once parameter nodes added, right click>Related Elements>Display Pins always shows at least one "unnamed" pin, even though the related property is named. Also, "unnamed" pins default to not showing type, but named pins show type.

sysml:Requirement.Text: The system must provide capability to elevate input water up to 2 meters from the source.
The system shall purify water by boiling it.

Describe a system for purifying dirty water. - Heat dirty water and condense steam are performed by a Counter Flow Heat Exchanger - Boil dirty water is performed by a Boiler. Drain residue is performed by a Drain. The water has properties: vol = 1 liter, density 1 gm/cm3, temp 20 deg C, specific heat 1cal/gm deg C, heat of vaporization 540 cal/gm.
The system shall purify dirty water.
Heat dirty water and condense steam are performed by a Counter Flow Heat Exchanger
Boil dirty water is performed by a Boiler.
Drain residue is performed by a Drain.
Water has properties: density 1 gm/cm3, temp 20 deg C, specific heat 1cal/gm deg C, heat of vaporization 540 cal/gm.
Water has an initial temp 20 deg C
The water distiller shall be able to operate at least 2 meters vertically above the source of dirty water.
